bdglue2

Class BDGluePropertyValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • bdglue2.BDGluePropertyValues

  • public final class BDGluePropertyValues
extends Object
    This class contains configuration constants used by the Big Data Glue code, including property names and where appropriate the default values to use in the event that a property is not defined.

      • ENCODER_DELIMITER

        public static final String ENCODER_DELIMITER
        The delimiter to use in Delimited Text encoding. Specify as a number that can be propertly parsed. This is because we want to support not only "typical" delimiters (comma, semicolon), but also binary delimiters such as the Hive default delimiter which is 001 (ASCII ctrl-A).

      • NUMERIC_ENCODING

        public static final String NUMERIC_ENCODING
        Set the type we should encode numeric/decimal types to. We need to have this flexibility because Avro does not support these types directly, so users will have to decide how they want this data represented on the other end: string, double, float, etc.
        See Also:

      • HEADER_ROWKEY

        public static final String HEADER_ROWKEY
        Boolean as to whether or not to include a value for the row's key as a concatenation of the key columns in the event header information. HBase and NoSQL KV API need the this. It is also needed if the publisher hash is based on key rather than table name.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HEADER_LONGNAME

        public static final String HEADER_LONGNAME
        Boolean as to whether or not to include the "long" table name in the header. FALSE will cause the "short" name to be included. Most prefer the long name. HBase and NoSQL prefer the short name.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HEADER_COLUMNFAMIILY

        public static final String HEADER_COLUMNFAMIILY
        Boolean as to whether or not to include a "columnFamily" value in the header. This is needed for Hbase.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HEADER_AVROPATH

        public static final String HEADER_AVROPATH
        Boolean as to whether or not to include the path to the Avro schema file in the header. This is needed for Avro encoding where Avro-formatted files are created in HDFS, including those that will be leveraged by Hive.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
